claim.claim-text:
16. The bag claim 14, wherein: 
said hood is connected to said first fastener strip at a connection region; 
said hood forms a closed end; 
said tear line has a first portion positioned between said mating profiles and said closed end; 
said tear line has a second portion positioned between said mating profiles and said connection region; and 
said tear line has a transition portion connecting said first portion to said second portion.

20. A method for making a tamper evident seal for a recloseable bag, comprising: 
providing first and second interlockable fastener strips; 
providing a first sheet of flexible film with first and second opposing parallel edges; 
scoring a first predetermined, non-linear repetitive pattern of weakening on the first sheet spaced apart from the first edge; 
scoring a second predetermined, non-linear repetitive pattern of weakening on the first sheet spaced apart from the second edge; 
attaching the first sheet of flexible film to the first fastener strip after said scoring the first pattern; and 
providing the assembly of fastener strips and first sheet for subsequent attachment to a second sheet of flexible film.

30. A method for making a recloseable bag, comprising: 
providing first and second interlockable fastener strips; 
providing a sheet of flexible film with first and second opposing parallel edges; 
scoring a first predetermined, non-linear repetitive pattern of weakening on the sheet spaced apart from the first edge; 
scoring a second predetermined, non-linear repetitive pattern of weakening on the sheet spaced apart from the second edge; 
attaching the sheet of flexible film to the first fastener strip after said scoring the first pattern; 
folding the sheet to form a bottom of the bag; and 
attaching the sheet of flexible film to the second fastener strip after said folding.
